g><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zft1665703132860.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zft1665703132860.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zft1665703132860.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zft1665703132860\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"zft1665703132860__ugetprofile_403668\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return a pointer to the name of the current <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span>\n      file.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"zft1665703132860__topic_d120422e1_d120423e1_d120424e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104zft1665703132860_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"zft1665703132860__codeblock_bp3_sj1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">unsigned char* ugetprofile (void);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zft1665703132860__topic_d85637e1_d85638e1_d85639e1_d85640e1_d85641e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d397885e64\">Parameters</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zft1665703132860__p_d120431e1_d120432e1_d120433e1\">None.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zft1665703132860__topic_d85642e1_d85643e1_d85644e1_d85645e1_d85646e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d397885e73\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zft1665703132860__p_d120437e1_d120438e1_d120439e1\">A pointer to the name of the current <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zft1665703132860__topic_d85647e1_d85648e1_d85649e1_d85650e1_d85651e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d397885e85\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zft1665703132860__d6421e20\">Microsoft Windows platforms only. In library\n          <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>. </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zft1665703132860__topic_d85652e1_d85653e1_d85654e1_d85655e1_d85656e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d397885e98\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zft1665703132860__p_d120449e1_d120450e1_d120451e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetprofile</code> returns a pointer to\n            the name of the current <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file. With this name, you can read and\n            write the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file yourself, using either Microsoft Windows API\n            calls such as <code class=\"ph codeph\">GetPrivateProfileString</code> and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">WritePrivateProfileString</code>, or the Uniface 3GL service functions\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ureadstringsyssetting</code> and\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">uwritestringsyssetting</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zft1665703132860__p_d120452e1_d120453e1_d120454e1\">The current <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file is usually <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">USYSADM:</span> directory, unless you use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">/ini</code> command line switch to specify another. Note that, even in this case, Uniface still reads the <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> file and uses it as a fallback resource when you retrieve data using <code class=\"ph codeph\">ureadstringsyssetting</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The following code puts the name of the current <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span>\n            file into the transcript window:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104zft1665703132860_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"zft1665703132860__codeblock_eql_wj1_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\nu_printf(\"Your current ini-file is %s\\n\", ugetprofile());</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eux1665703132929.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ureadstringsyssetting</a><p>Read a string from the specified section of a specified ini file.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsu1665703133058.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uwritestringsyssetting</a><p>Copies a string to a specified section of a specified ini file.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534427\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534427\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ugetprofile Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Return a pointer to the name of the current .ini file. Explain this code unsigned char* ugetprofile (void); Copy Parameters None. Return Values A pointer to the name of the current .ini file. Use Microsoft Windows platforms only. In library yrtl . Description ugetprofile returns a pointer to the name of the current .ini file. With this name, you can read and write the .ini file yourself, using either Microsoft Windows API calls such as GetPrivateProfileString and WritePrivateProfileString , or the Uniface 3GL service functions ureadstringsyssetting and uwritestringsyssetting . The current .ini file is usually usys.ini in the USYSADM: directory, unless you use the /ini command line switch to specify another. Note that, even in this case, Uniface still reads the usys.ini file and uses it as a fallback resource when you retrieve data using ureadstringsyssetting . The following code puts the name of the current .ini file into the transcript window: Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> u_printf(\"Your current ini-file is %s\\n\", ugetprofile()); Copy Related Links ureadstringsyssetting Read a string from the specified section of a specified ini file. uwritestringsyssetting Copies a string to a specified section of a specified ini file. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}